HEADWORD: Burgee
<hw>Bur"gee</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind
of small coat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A swallow-tailed flag; a
distinguishing pennant, used by cutters, yachts, and merchant
vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burgeois</ent>⟦br⟧
